Requirements
*************
chromedriver
Python 3.6


Instructions to execute the automation
**************************************

1- create a virtualenvironment

py -3 -m venv /path/to/environment

2- activate environment

Execute script /path/to/environment/Scripts/activate , according to your O.S system

3-  install dependencies

pip3 install -r requirements

4-  Edit the configuration file

cd conf/

Edit the file conf_tuenti.yml

	- Set the absolute path to the webdriver in the driver section. By default the application will use chromedriver. Optionally Firefox, or IE can be used, by changing the key "chrome" by "firefox" or "explorer"

	- Set the dataset in the credentials section according to the user and url that will be tested with.